20Dimon%2C%20Chairman%20and%20CEO%20of%20JPMorgan%20Chase%2C%20testifies%20during%20a%20Senate%20Banking%20Committee%20hearing%20at%20the%20Hart%20Senate%20Office%20Building%20on%20December%2006%2C%202023%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a11c3e6979d7371822bcc9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELoren%20Elliott%2FGetty%20Images%3B%20Win%20McNamee%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJPMorgan%20CEO%20Jamie%20Dimon%20isn't%20happy%20about%20the%20way%20things%20are%20playing%20out%20in%20San%20Francisco.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20city%C2%A0%26quot%3Bis%20in%20far%20worse%20shape%20than%20New%20York%26quot%3B%20and%20needs%20lower%20rents%20to%20attract%20workers%2C%20he%20told%20Fox%20Business.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESan%20Francisco's%20population%20fell%207.5%25%20over%20the%20pandemic.%20People%20say%20crime%20and%20rent%20are%20pushing%20them%20away.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESan%20Francisco%20%26quot%3Bis%20in%20far%20worse%20shape%20than%20New%20York%2C%26quot%3B%20Jamie%20Dimon%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20JPMorgan%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foxbusiness.com%2Fvideo%2F6344553905112%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFox%20Business%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20in%20the%20city%20for%20his%20company's%20annual%20healthcare%20conference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsked%20by%20%26quot%3BMornings%20with%20Maria%26quot%3B%20host%20Maria%20Bartiromo%20about%20his%20thoughts%20on%20San%20Francisco%2C%20Dimon%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BAny%20city%20who%20doesn't%20do%20a%20good%20job%2C%20it%20will%20lose%20its%20population.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou've%20seen%20some%20cities%20do%20a%20great%20job%20%E2%80%A6%20and%20some%20cities%20do%20a%20terrible%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFeatures%20that%20make%20a%20city%20attractive%20include%20parks%2C%20art%2C%20safety%2C%20jobs%2C%20and%20affordable%20housing%2C%20Dimon%20said.%20San%20Francisco%20needs%20more%20affordable%20housing%20so%20that%20companies%20can%20attract%20workers%20and%20create%20jobs%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20been%20an%20exodus%20of%20both%20workers%20and%20high-profile%20businesses%20from%20San%20Francisco%20in%20recent%20years%20as%20it%20battles%20with%20a%20reputation%20crisis%20amid%20a%20swirl%20of%20media%20reporting%20on%20the%20city's%20supposed%20demise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESan%20Francisco's%20population%20was%20around%20873%2C000%20as%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fquickfacts%2Ffact%2Ftable%2Fsanfranciscocitycalifornia%2CUS%2FPST045222%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2020%20Census%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20estimates%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fdata%2Ftables%2Ftime-series%2Fdemo%2Fpopest%2F2020s-total-cities-and-towns.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECensus%20Bureau%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggest%20that%20it%20fell%20to%20about%20811%2C000%20in%202021%20and%20808%2C000%20in%202022%2C%20a%20drop%20of%20around%207.5%25.%20People%20flocked%20from%20the%20city%20for%20a%20plethora%20of%20reasons%2C%20such%20as%20to%20avoid%20crime%2C%20find%20cheaper%20rent%2C%20and%20escape%20the%20hustle%20and%20bustle%2C%20ultimately%20enabled%20by%20the%20surge%20in%20remote%20work%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20business%20owners%2C%20residents%2C%20and%20visitors%20have%20expressed%20concern%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbob-lee-stabbing-murder-san-francisco-crime-data-square-block-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eviolent%20crime%2C%20drugs%2C%20and%20homelessness%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20the%20city%2C%20though%20the%20rate%20of%20homelessness%20in%20San%20Francisco%20fell%20during%20the%20pandemic%20and%20is%20actually%20lower%20than%20in%20Oakland%20and%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sf.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2023-07%2F2023%2520Homelessness%2520Benchmarking%2520Report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecity%20data%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20rent%20and%20property%20prices%20in%20San%20Francisco%20are%20much%20higher%20than%20the%20US%20average.%20Households%20also%20spend%20considerably%20more%20on%20food%2C%20insurance%2C%20and%20pension%20contributions%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fregions%2Fwest%2Fsummary%2Fblssummary_sanfrancisco.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%20shows%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20some%20indicators%20paint%20a%20different%20picture%20of%20San%20Francisco's%20economy.%20Unemployment%20in%20San%20Francisco%20has%20risen%20dramatically%20over%20the%20past%20year%20but%20is%20equal%20to%20the%20US%20average%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fregions%2Fwest%2Fsummary%2Fblssummary_sanfrancisco.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fquickfacts%2Ffact%2Ftable%2Fsanfranciscocitycalifornia%2CUS%2FPST045222%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECensus%20Bureau%20estimates%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%202022%20suggest%20that%20San%20Francisco%20has%20twice%20the%20US'%20average%20per%20capita%20income%20and%20a%20significantly%20higher%20proportion%20of%20residents%20with%20bachelor's%20degrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20mayor%20has%20worked%20aggressively%20to%20ramp%20up%20and%20expand%20the%20city's%20public%20safety%20efforts%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20including%20prioritizing%20a%20recovering%20economy%20and%20workforce%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20San%20Francisco%20mayor%20London%20Breed%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsfstandard.com%2F2024%2F01%2F11%2Fjamie-dimon-san-francisco-jpmorgan-chase-conference%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20San%20Francisco%20Standard%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20response%20to%20Dimon's%20comments.%20%