20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22250%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03150954%2FPrism.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F03150954%2FPrism-150x150.png%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691446%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22250%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJaitley%E2%80%99s%20speech%20was%20not%20too%20different%20from%20that%20of%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20public%20accounts%20committee%2C%20Professor%20K.V.%20Thomas.%20If%20Thomas%20advised%20the%20CAG%20not%20to%20indulge%20in%20reporting%20%E2%80%98notional%20losses%E2%80%99%2C%20Jaitley%20advised%20the%20CAG%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fnorth%2Fstory%2Farun-jaitley-cag-2g-spectrum-scam-coalgate-225074-2014-10-30%5C%22%3Enot%20to%20hype%20its%20audit%20findings%20for%20media%20attention%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20remarks%20showed%20how%20much%20politicians%20really%20care%20about%20this%20constitutional%20institution.%20Ironically%2C%20the%20theme%20of%20the%20conference%20was%20%E2%80%98Promoting%20Good%20Governance%20and%20Accountability%20Through%20Audit%E2%80%99!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20late%20Ramaswamy%20R.%20Iyer%20had%20pointed%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Fop-ed%2Fcomment-a-constitutional-impropriety%2Farticle6545482.ece%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cconstitutional%20impropriety%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20chairman%E2%80%99s%20remarks%20and%20argued%20that%20the%20constitution%20grants%20the%20CAG%20and%20the%20Indian%20Accounts%20and%20Audit%20Department%20(IAAD)%20complete%20autonomy%20in%20deciding%20the%20scope%20of%20an%20audit%20exercise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20months%20before%20that%20volte-face%20by%20Jaitley%2C%20in%20August%202014%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2FIndia%2FCAG-seeks-RTI-powers-to-access-govt-records%2Farticleshow%2F40384024.cms%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20CAG%20Shashi%20Kant%20Sharma%20had%20written%20to%20the%20Union%20finance%20minister%20%E2%80%9Cdemanding%20that%20the%20national%20auditor%20should%20be%20given%20RTI%20powers%20to%20access%20information%20and%20a%20penal%20provision%20should%20be%20included%20in%20the%20existing%20%5BCAG%20Act%5D%20to%20make%20it%20mandatory%20for%20furnishing%20of%20information%20%5Bby%20the%20executive%5D%20in%20a%20time-bound%20manner%E2%80%9D%20(as%20paraphrased%20by%20%3Cem%3ETOI%3C%2Fem%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftransparency-in-modi-era-cags-working-shows-it-remains-opaque%5C%22%3ETransparency%20in%20Modi%20Era%3F%20CAG%E2%80%99s%20Working%20Shows%20It%20Remains%20Opaque%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20letter%20dated%20June%202014%20underlined%20that%20the%20proposed%20amendments%20had%20been%20under%20the%20finance%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20consideration%20for%20the%20preceding%20five%20years%20(i.e.%202009-2014).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20proposed%20draft%20amendment%20Bill%20to%20give%20the%20IAAD%20adequate%20powers%20was%20first%20submitted%20in%20November%202009.%20The%20CAG%E2%80%99s%20office%20had%20made%20subsequent%20revisions%20to%20the%20Bill%20based%20on%20suggestions%20by%20the%20finance%20ministry%2C%20and%20submitted%20a%20revised%20Bill%20in%20February%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20one%20looks%20at%20the%20debates%20of%20the%20constituent%20assembly%20of%20India%20while%20it%20framed%20the%20constitution%2C%20one%20will%20understand%20that%20the%20CAG%20and%20the%20IAAD%20were%20imagined%20as%20being%20independent%20of%20and%20autonomous%20from%20executive%20interference.%20So%2C%20such%20a%20dialogic%20and%20consultative%20approach%20should%20have%20evoked%20a%20positive%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESadly%2C%20there%20had%20been%20complete%20silence%20from%20the%20ministry%20on%20this%20important%20matter.%20Jaitley%20and%20his%20party%20failed%20to%20give%20more%20powers%20to%20this%20constitutional%20institution%20during%20their%20first%20year%20in%20office%2C%20and%20the%20proposed%20amendments%20have%20not%20been%20in%20introduced%20in%20parliament%20till%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStrong%20audit%20findings%2C%20zero%20consequences%3A%20environment%20clearances%20and%20post-clearance%20monitoring%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2010%2C%202017%2C%20a%20performance%20audit%20on%20%E2%80%98Environmental%20Clearances%20and%20Post-Clearance%20Monitoring%20Mechanism%E2%80%99%20was%20tabled%20in%20parliament.%20While%20the%20audit%20findings%20and%20recommendations%20clearly%20pointed%20to%20the%20need%20to%20strengthen%20compliance%20with%20environmental%20regulations%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20actions%20have%20brazenly%20undermined%20this%20sane%20advice%20from%20the%20national%20auditor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrowing%20these%20findings%20away%2C%20the%20NDA%20government%20continued%20its%20race%20to%20the%20bottom%20in%20diluting%20environmental%20laws%20and%20facilitating%20the%20corporate%20takeover%20of%20natural%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adaniwatch.org%2Faudit_body_headed_by_modi_confidante_slams_approval_of_adani_port_expansion_at_dahej%5C%22%3Eperformance%20audit%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98Conservation%20of%20Coastal%20Ecosystems%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20tabled%20in%20parliament%20on%20August%208%2C%202022%20also%20pointed%20out%20brazen%20non-compliance%20with%20the%20EIA%20notification%20by%20Adani%E2%80%99s%20port%20expansion%20at%20Dahej.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F_BDqVanVhZo%3Fsi%3DZGrFC_-iQ4ivqy7Q%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERedacted%20audit%20reports%20on%20defence%20deals%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CAG%E2%80%99s%20audit%20report%20on%20Rafale%20has%20come%20under%20criticism%20for%20agreeing%20to%20editorial%20cuts%20from%20the%20audited%20entity%20on%20the%20matter%20of%20pricing.%20Usually%2C%20audit%20reports%20on%20defence%20matters%20only%20undergo%20such%20redaction%20as%20part%20of%20the%20protection%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20strategic%20interests.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Frafale-and-the-cag-a-case-of-redaction-ad-absurdum%5C%22%3EAnalysts%20believe%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20redactions%20in%20the%20Rafale%20report%20went%20much%20beyond%20such%20usual%20suggestions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAudit%20reports%20that%20were%20planned%20but%20never%20saw%20the%20light%20of%20the%20day%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20Josy%20Joseph%2C%20Shashi%20Kant%20Sharma%20had%20talked%20about%20undertaking%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Finterview%2Fwe-will-seek-audit-of-the-fiscal-impact-of-demonetisation%2Farticle17424354.ece%5C%22%3Ean%20audit%20of%20the%20fiscal%20impact%20of%20demonetisation%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20his%20successor%20Rajiv%20Mehrishi%2C%20who%20took%20over%20on%20September%2025%2C%202017%2C%20did%20not%20pursue%20this%20thematic%20audit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDelayed%20audit%20reports%20and%20reduced%20output%20marked%20Rajiv%20Mehrishi%E2%80%99s%20years%20as%20CAG%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20before%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20impacted%20work%20at%20the%20national%20audit%20office%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fcag-delayed-audit-reports-lower-output-defence-services%5C%22%3Ethere%20were%20signs%20that%20the%20machinery%20was%20slowing%20down%3C%2Fa%3E.%20During%20the%20year%202017-18%2C%20the%20CAG%20prepared%20only%2098%20audit%20reports%20in%20total%2C%20and%20in%202018-19%2C%20it%20prepared%20only%2073%20audit%20reports%20in%20total.%20In%202020%2C%20Mehrishi%20signed%20a%20bulk%20of%20audit%20reports%20in%20his%20last%20week%20in%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20slowing%20down%20of%20the%20auditing%20processes%20since%202017%20was%20also%20accompanied%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F967903%2Ftabling-of-cag-reports-in-parliament-is-frequently-being-delayed-helping-government-evade-scrutiny%5C%22%3Eprolonged%20delays%20in%20the%20tabling%20of%20audit%20reports%20in%20parliament%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20ruling%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENon-transparent%20process%20of%20selecting%20the%20CAG%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20years%2C%20concerned%20citizens%20have%20been%20left%20wondering%20if%20the%20by%20process%20by%20which%20the%20CAG%20is%20selected%20is%20completely%20arbitrary%20and%20goes%20against%20the%20grain%20of%20what%20was%20envisaged%20during%20the%20debates%20of%20the%20constituent%20assembly%20of%20India%20while%20framing%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESelecting%20a%20senior%20administrative%20services%20officer%20who%20has%20worked%20in%20proximity%20to%20those%20in%20the%20ruling%20dispensation%20does%20raise%20certain%20doubts%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20the%20public.%20Sometimes%20this%20arbitrary%20process%2C%20wherein%20the%20prime%20minister%20suggests%20to%20the%20president%20one%20name%20out%20of%20a%20shortlist%20prepared%20by%20the%20cabinet%2C%20creates%20an%20obvious%20conflict%20of%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcag-selection-auditor-prime-minister-government%5C%22%3EThe%20Process%20of%20Selecting%20the%20CAG%20Cannot%20Evade%20Accountability%20%E2%80%93%20Like%20it%20Has%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETweaking%20of%20follow-up%20performance%20audit%20plans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsually%2C%20the%20senior%20management%20of%20the%20CAG%E2%80%99s%20office%20undertakes%20follow-up%20performance%20audits%20every%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fquestions-cag-auditors-failed-to-probe-in-its-mizoram-report%5C%22%3Efunctioning%20of%20the%20Building%20and%20Other%20Construction%20Workers%E2%80%99%20Welfare%20Boards%3C%2Fa%3E%20(BOCWWBs)%20across%20states%20and%20Union%20territories%20came%20under%20a%20comprehensive%20performance%20audit%20during%20the%20activity%20year%202008-09%20(reviewing%20their%20performance%20between%202003%20and%202008)%2C%20the%20next%20follow-up%20performance%20audit%20across%20states%20would%20take%20place%20during%20the%20activity%20year%202013-14%20(reviewing%20performance%20between%202008%20and%202013).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20follow-up%20performance%20audits%20have%20not%20been%20taken%20up%20across%20all%20states.%20This%20is%20strange%20and%20points%20to%20the%20lethargic%20attitude%20of%20the%20leadership.%20The%20pandemic%20year%20(2020-21)%20made%20it%20all%20the%20more%20crucial%20to%20know%20whether%20the%20BOCWWBs%20met%20their%20stated%20goals%20of%20providing%20social%20protection%20to%20our%20migrant%20construction%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECentrally%20sponsored%20schemes%20not%20audited%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20article%20titled%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fopinion%2Fcag-could-have-done-better%2Farticle67533089.ece%5C%22%3ECAG%20could%20have%20done%20better%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20Govind%20Bhattacharjee%20has%20pointed%20out%20that%20%E2%80%9Cexcept%20%5Bthe%5D%20PMAY%2C%20reports%20of%20which%20are%20available%20till%202022%2C%20and%20PM%20Kisan%2C%20%5Bthe%20performance%20audit%20of%20which%20is%5D%20understood%20to%20be%20underway%2C%20none%20of%20the%20other%20centrally%20sponsored%20schemes%20have%20been%20audited%20beyond%20the%20fiscal%20year%202018.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOutstanding%20action%20taken%20notes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20audit%20paragraph%2C%20once%20finalised%20and%20figuring%20in%20an%20audit%20report%20that%20gets%20tabled%20in%20parliament%20or%20a%20legislative%20assembly%2C%20requires%20the%20audited%20entity%20to%20initiate%20corrective%20measures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAudited%20entities%20are%20required%20to%20submit%20%E2%80%98action%20taken%20notes%E2%80%99%20to%20the%20CAG.%20Non-submission%20of%20such%20action%20taken%20notes%2C%20with%20delays%20running%20into%20years%2C%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20augur%20well%20for%20audit%20findings%20leading%20to%20improved%20governance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20the%20conspicuous%20decision%20to%20not%20even%20report%20the%20number%20of%20outstanding%20action%20taken%20notes%20or%20audit%20paragraphs%20is%20a%20cause%20for%20concern.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fy5w51%2F4%2F%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22492%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYear-wise%20audit%20reports%20approved%20by%20the%20CAG%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2010-11%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Total%20Reports%3A%20221%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2011-12%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20102%20reports%20on%20state%20governments%2C%2035%20reports%20on%20the%20Union%20government.%20Total%20Reports%3A%20137%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2012-13%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Total%20reports%3A%20138%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2013-14%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20102%20reports%20on%20state%20governments%2C%2032%20reports%20on%20the%20Union%20government.%20Total%20reports%3A%20134%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2015-16%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20135%20reports%20on%20state%20governments%2C%2053%20reports%20on%20the%20Union%20government.%20Total%20reports%3A%20188%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2016-17%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20101%20reports%20on%20state%20governmen