bels%20inaccurately%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20critical%20roles%20each%20spouse%20plays%20in%20a%20family%20and%20partnership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20There's%20no%20clear%20guidance%20on%20how%20couples%20can%20navigate%20in%20this%20arena%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20found%20no%20guidebook%2C%20no%20resources%2C%20no%20support%20groups%2C%20and%20few%20best%20practices%20to%20help%20couples%20figure%20this%20out.%20There%20are%20countless%20resources%20on%20how%20to%20get%20my%20toddler%20to%20eat%20veggies%2C%20but%20nothing%20on%20this%20modern%20arrangement%20of%20household%20duties%20and%20how%20a%20couple%20might%20need%20to%20fight%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgender-norms-disrupted-my-daughters-first-friendship-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehistorical%20gender%20norms%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20I'm%20in%20a%20frequent%20tug-of-war%20between%20my%20kids%20and%20my%20job%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20parent%20and%20with%20that%20comes%20a%20natural%20desire%20to%20be%20an%20active%20part%20of%20my%20kids'%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20kids%20expect%20me%20to%20be%20everywhere%20and%20anywhere%20%E2%80%94%20and%20as%20present%20as%20most%20stay-at-home%20providers%20%E2%80%94%20because%20that's%20what%20they%20see%20around%20them.%20This%20creates%20undue%20pressure%2C%20expectation%2C%20guilt%2C%20and%20disappointment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20there's%20a%20conflict%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-schedule-your-day-when-you-run-your-own-business-2016-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escheduling%2C%20priorities%2C%20or%20availability%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20because%20I'm%20the%20breadwinner%2C%20I%20often%20must%20choose%20the%20professional%20demand.%20It's%20hard%20when%20I%20want%20to%20be%20in%20two%20places%20at%20once%2C%20and%20then%20it%20feels%20like%20my%20options%20are%20limited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20natural%20outcomes%2C%20like%20my%20little%20kids%20preferring%20my%20husband.%20My%20husband%20typically%20gets%20to%20hear%20about%20the%20big%20moments%20first%20and%20naturally%2C%20he%20gets%20to%20be%20more%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20My%20husband%20is%20around%20women%20all%20the%20time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20spends%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20with%20beautiful%2C%20smart%2C%20funny%20women%20with%20shared%20interests%20while%20I%20spend%20a%20disproportionate%20amount%20of%20time%20with%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20an%20extra%20faithful%20solid%20relationship%2C%20and%20I'm%20not%20worried%20at%20all%20about%20my%20husband%20acting%20inappropriately%20%E2%80%94%20for%20us%2C%20it's%20not%20about%20that.%20It's%20about%20what%20our%20adult%20friendships%20look%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20extra%20work%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-friends-as-adult-moving-cities-nyc-la-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20make%20friends%20as%20an%20adult%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20when%20the%20pool%20of%20people%20you're%20exposed%20to%20is%20limited%2C%20it%20makes%20it%20less%20likely%20for%20him%20to%20connect%20with%20adult%20friends%20from%20this%20stage%20of%20life.%20It%20can%20be%20a%20little%20lonely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20My%20friends%20make%20assumptions%20about%20my%20marriage%20and%20don't%20always%20understand%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20are%20confident%20in%20our%20choice%2C%20people%20assume%20my%20husband%20is%20less%20successful%20and%20less%20motivated%20since%20he%20isn't%20the%20financial%20provider%20for%20our%20family.%20They%20assume%20he%20didn't%20or%20couldn't%20%26quot%3Bmake%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20worst%20part%20is%20that%20my%20friends%20don't%20always%20understand%20the%20demands%20of%20being%20a%20breadwinner.%20As%20a%20mom%2C%20I%20share%20many%20feelings%20with%20them%2C%20but%20I%20also%20share%20the%20same%20demands%20as%20the%20historical%20%26quot%3Bprovider%26quot%3B%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20no%2C%20I%20can't%20necessarily%20allocate%20the%20same%20time%20volunteering%2C%20being%20available%20on%20Wednesday%20for%20brunch%2C%20or%20being%20at%20school%20pickup.%20I%20often%20get%20grief%20from%20friends%20for%20not%20replying%20to%20texts.%20Well%2C%20I%20was%20busy%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20in%20my%20life%20is%20supportive.%20I'm%20just%20not%20always%20sure%20they%20understand%20many%20of%20the%20things%20I'm%20thinking%20and%20worrying%20about%20%E2%80%94%20I%20have%20this%20whole%20other%20to-do%20list%20and%20pressures%20behind%20the%20scenes%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-provider-stay-at-home-dad-husband-kids-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705054381000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659d901fec62ab5daf8200de%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-provider-stay-at-home-dad-husband-kids-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20mom%20of%20four%20is%20the%20breadwinner%20and%20her%20husband%20is%20a%20stay-at-home%20dad%2C%20but%20she%20says%20these%20terms%20are%20outdated%20and%20inaccurate.%20She%20shares%20the%20best%20and%20worst%20parts%20of%20this%20role.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Robin%20Madell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-provider-stay-at-home-dad-husband-kids-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20invested%20enough%20money%20to%20retire%20at%2029.%20I%20don't%20ever%20need%20to%20worry%20about%20earning%20a%20salary%20again.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22816%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Daniel%20George%20traveling%20in%20Iceland.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659fd27fdcdb354a98569eaf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22612%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDaniel%20George%20traveling%20in%20Iceland.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Daniel%20George%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDaniel%20George%20got%20a%20job%20at%20Google%20X%20with%20a%20six-figure%20salary%20after%20finishing%20his%20doctoral%20studies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20put%20most%20of%20his%20income%20in%20tax-advantaged%20accounts%20or%20invested%20it%20in%20stocks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAt%2029%2C%20George%20realized%20he%20had%20enough%20money%20saved%20and%20invested%20to%20retire%2C%20but%20he%20started%20a%20company.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20an%20as-told-to%20story%20with%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrhackernomad.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDaniel%20George%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20startup%20founder%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fdan7geo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eformer%20vice%20president%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20at%20JPMorgan.%20This%20transcript%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20clarity%20and%20length.%20George%20provided%20documents%20to%20verify%20his%20finances.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20I%20thought%20about%20retiring%20early%2C%20I%20was%2024.%20I'd%20just%20gotten%20a%20job%20at%20Google%20X%20after%20a%20summer%20internship.%20My%20starting%20total%20compensation%20would%20be%20%24265%2C000%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20did%20the%20math%20and%20realized%20that%20after%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20of%20saving%20I%20could%20easily%20go%20back%20to%20India%20and%20retire%20if%20I%20wanted%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20working%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-layoff-moonshot-x-development-sergey-brin-larry-page-astro-2023-01%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGoogle%20X%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20was%20a%20Ph.D.%20student%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Illinois%20in%20Champaign.%20I%20finished%20my%20Ph.D.%20in%20December%202018%20with%20%24100%2C000%20in%20savings.%20Throughout%20my%20doctorate%20I'd%20received%20money%20from%20fellowships%20and%20awards%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20six%20figure-income%20working%20part%20time%20for%20tech%20companies%2C%C2%A0including%20my%20internship%20at%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20begun%20cautiously%20investing%20in%20several%20tech%20stocks%2C%20including%20Google%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fapple%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EApple%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Famazon%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAmazon%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fnvda-stock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENvidia%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Ftesla%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETesla%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20only%20putting%20a%20few%20thousand%20dollars%20in%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20my%20money%20went%20into%20my%20bank%20account%2C%20earning%20little%20interest.%20I%20didn't%20know%20much%20about%20finance%20and%20was%20afraid%20to%20invest%20too%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGoogle%20changed%20my%20perspective%20on%20savings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20for%20Google%20X%20was%20my%20dream%20job.%20It%20was%20like%20working%20in%20a%20magical%20fairyland.%20There%20was%20unlimited%20food%20and%20drinks%20and%20amazing%20facilities%2C%20including%20ping-pong%20tables%2C%20video-game%20rooms%2C%20soccer%20fields%2C%20a%20gym%2C%20tennis%20courts%2C%20and%20free%20massages%20in%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20immediately%20accepted%20the%20full-time%20offer%20in%20August%202018%20to%20start%20as%20a%20Google%20X%20employee%2C%20moving%20into%20a%20shared%20apartment%20in%20Mountain%20View%2C%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20year%20at%20Google%2C%20I%20started%20teaching%20myself%20more%20about%20finances%20and%20taxes.%20I%20was%20making%20more%20money%20than%20ever%20before%20but%20paying%20nearly%2050%25%20in%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20taught%20myself%20about%20retirement%20accounts%20like%20Roth%20IRAs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20first%20learned%20how%20to%20optimize%20my%20retirement%20accounts%20to%20minimize%20my%20tax%20liability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20should%20max%20out%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E401(k)%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20this%20means%20investing%20as%20much%20money%20as%20possible%20into%20your%20retirement%20accounts.%20This%20is%20about%20%2420%2C000%20a%20year%20in%20the%20US%20plus%20how%20much%20your%20company%20matches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20you%20reach%20this%20limit%2C%20you%20can%20use%20the%20%26quot%3Bmega%20backdoor%20Roth%20401(k)%26quot%3B%20strategy%20at%20some%20companies%20to%20put%20an%20additional%20after-tax%20income%20into%20an%20401(k)%20account%20and%20roll%20it%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-roth-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoth%20401(k)%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20401(k)s%2C%20you%20can%20contribute%20%246%2C500%20into%20an%20IRA%20and%20immediately%20convert%20it%20into%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-roth-ira%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoth%20IRA%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20using%20the%20%26quot%3Bbackdoor%20Roth%20IRA%26quot%3B%20strategy%20to%20bypass%20the%20income%20restrictions%20that%20typically%20prevent%20high%20earners%20from%20contributing%20to%20Roth%20IRAs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20have%20a%20qualified%20health-insurance%20plan%2C%20you%20can%20also%20contribute%20over%20%244%2C000%20each%20year%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-use-health-savings-account-hsa-investing-retirement%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealth%20savings%20account%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Doing%20so%20has%20three%20advantages%3A%20The%20money%20gets%20deducted%20from%20your%20taxable%20income%2C%20it%20grows%20tax-free%20from%20when%20you%20invest%20it%2C%20and%20it%20is%20tax-free%20when%20you%20finally%20withdraw%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20put%20much%20of%20my%20income%20in%20tax%3C%2Fstrong%3E-%3Cstrong%3Eadvantaged%20accounts%20and%20stocks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20working%20at%20Google%2C%20I%20spent%20less%20than%2010%25%20of%20my%20income%20on%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20walked%20or%20biked%20to%20work%2C%20so%20I%20never%20bought%20a%20car.%20I%20ate%20three%20meals%20daily%20at%20Google%2C%20so%20I%20rarely%20paid%20for%20food.%20Even%20though%20housing%20is%20usually%20very%20expensive%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20my%20rent%20was%20quite%20low%20because%20I%20was%20splitting%20an%20apartment%20with%20my%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20I%20knew%20bought%20expensive%20cars%20or%20houses%2C%20but%20I%20decided%20to%20invest%20most%20of%20my%20earnings.%20The%20more%20I%20saved%20early%20on%2C%20the%20longer%20my%20money%20had%20to%20grow%20and%20compound%20exponentially.%20I%20could%20always%20move%20to%20low-cost-of-living%20cities%20and%20buy%20a%20much%20nicer%20house%20later.%20I%20was%20still%20having%20a%20great%20time%20at%20Google%20and%20never%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20sacrificing%20my%20quality%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20invested%20over%20%2475%2C000%20yearly%20into%20the%20tax-advantaged%20accounts%20and%20even%20more%20in%20my%20regular%20stockbroker%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20could've%20retired%20to%20my%20home%20country%2C%20India%2C%20by%2026%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202020%2C%20at%20age%2026%2C%20I%20knew%20that%20I%20could%20retire%20and%20move%20home%20to%20India%20if%20I%20wanted%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20rule%20of%20thumb%20in%20the%20FIRE%20community%20%E2%80%94%20which%20stands%20for%20financial%20independence%2C%20retire%20early%20%E2%80%94%20that%20you%20can%20retire%20when%20you're%20spending%20less%20than%204%25%20of%20your%20net%20investments%20each%20year%2C%20or%203%25%20if%20you're%20very%20young.%20I%20had%20over%20%24500%2C000%20invested%2C%20enough%20to%20afford%20to%20move%20using%20that%20rule.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20I%20had%20just%20started%20dating%20my%20future%20wife%2C%20an%20AI%20scientist%20at%20Google%20X%20who%20was%20American.%20I%20knew%20I'd%20need%20to%20save%20much%20more%20to%20retire%20early%20and%20be%20able%20to%20live%20in%20the%20US%20with%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22963%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Daniel%20George%20proposed%20to%20his%20wife%20in%20front%20of%20the%20Taj%20Mahal.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659fd2f76979d73718225a69%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGeorge%20proposed%20to%20his%20wife%20in%20front%20of%20the%20Taj%20Mahal.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Daniel%20George%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20becoming%20more%20interested%20in%20investing%20when%20JPMorgan%20reached%20out%20to%20me%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%202020%2C%20a%20few%20friends%20and%20I%20started%20a%20side%20project%20developing%20machine-learning%20algorithms%20that%20automatically%20trade%20stocks.%20We%20deployed%20it%2C%20and%20my%20investments%20doubled%20in%20four%20months.%20On%20the%20back%20of%20this%20success%2C%20I%20became%20increasingly%20obsessed%20with%20finance%2C%20trading%2C%20and%20investing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%202020%2C%20a%20JPMorgan%20recruiter%20offered%20me%2