3-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E136%20other%20engineering%20managers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20axed%20by%20LinkedIn%20in%20October%20as%20part%20of%20sweeping%20700-person%20job%20cuts%20%E2%80%94%20the%20first%20to%20directly%20affect%20engineering%20teams.%20The%20company%20had%20earlier%20laid%20off%20716%20sales%2C%20operations%2C%20and%20support%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eworkers%20in%20May.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20spoke%20with%2013%20other%20current%20and%20former%20employees%2C%20who%20said%20the%20job%20cuts%20followed%20a%20swift%20tightening%20up%20at%20the%20company%20and%20a%20dramatic%20shift%20from%20the%20LinkedIn%20of%20the%20past.%20They%20requested%20anonymity%20as%20they%20weren't%20authorized%20to%20speak%20to%20the%20media%2C%20but%20their%20identities%20have%20been%20verified%20by%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20other%20tech%20firms%2C%20LinkedIn%20and%20its%20employees%20benefited%20from%20a%20decade%20of%20ZIRP%2C%20the%20zero-interest%20rate%20environment%20that%20led%20to%20lofty%20tech%20valuations%2C%20which%20gave%20rise%20to%20big%20salaries%20and%20splashy%20perks.%20The%20effects%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F04%2F30%2Ftechnology%2Fbig-tech-pandemic.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompounded%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20COVID-19%2C%20as%20millions%20of%20people%20spent%20the%20majority%20of%20their%20time%20online%20during%20lockdowns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-big-tech-companies-laying-off-spoiled-workers-perks-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20ZIRP%20era%3C%2Fa%3E%20ended.%20Inflation%20took%20hold.%20Interest%20rates%20shot%20up.%20Nearly%20half%20a%20million%20employees%20are%20estimated%20to%20have%20lost%20their%20jobs%20at%20tech%20companies%20over%20the%20last%20two%20years.%20Satya%20Nadella%2C%20CEO%20of%20LinkedIn's%20parent%20company%20Microsoft%2C%20said%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fread-email-microsoft-ceo-sent-employees-announcing-10000-job-cuts-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20January%202023%20memo%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20companies%20were%20cutting%20back%20on%20digital%20spend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pain%20of%20this%20shift%20was%20felt%20across%20Big%20Tech%20companies%2C%20but%20it%20was%20particularly%20shocking%20at%20LinkedIn%2C%20which%20was%20known%20for%20what%20some%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Brest%20and%20vest%26quot%3B%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20years%2C%20there%20was%20a%20semi-joke%20that%20some%20people%20in%20Big%20Tech%20go%20to%20LinkedIn%20to%20retire%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20current%20engineer%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20very%20rare%20to%20get%20fired%20or%20let%20go%20at%20LinkedIn%20in%20the%20past.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ENow%2C%20according%20to%20another%20current%20worker%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20still%20have%20a%20monopoly%20in%20the%20space%2C%20but%20to%20achieve%20the%20same%20level%20of%20growth%20we've%20had%20in%20the%20past%2C%20more%20work%20has%20to%20be%20put%20in.%20It's%20not%20an%20easy%20win%20anymore.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20those%20stressors%20have%20trickled%20down%20to%20the%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20worker%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmid%20a%20transformative%20year%20for%20the%20social%20network%2C%20LinkedIn%20spokesperson%20Nicole%20Leverich%20said%20the%20company%20has%20continued%20to%20prioritize%20its%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLinkedIn's%20culture%20and%20values%C2%A0continue%20to%20be%20our%20competitive%20advantage%2C%20especially%20as%20we%20come%20off%20a%20record%20year%20where%20our%20talented%20team%20came%20together%20to%20transform%20how%201%20billion%20people%20use%20LinkedIn%20to%20learn%2C%20sell%2C%20and%20get%20hired%2C%26quot%3B%20Leverich%20said%20in%20an%20emailed%20statement.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20while%20we're%20adapting%20the%20way%20we%20work%20to%20meet%20new%20opportunities%2C%20our%20number%20one%20priority%20is%20always%20our%20talent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20golden%20days%20of%20growth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20LinkedIn%20workers%20like%20to%20reminisce%20about%20what%20one%20engineer%20called%20the%20%26quot%3Bgolden%20days.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAfter%20the%20professional%20network%20was%20acquired%20by%20Microsoft%20in%202016%2C%20its%20annual%20revenue%20growth%20was%20in%20the%20double%20digits.%20Some%20of%20that%20growth%20coincided%20with%20the%20pandemic%2C%20when%20many%20of%20LinkedIn's%20most%20engaged%20users%20were%20stuck%20at%20home%2C%20on%20their%20laptops%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-everyone-is-quitting-great-resignation-psychologist-pandemic-rethink-life-2021-10%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eand%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20job%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20employees%2C%20benefits%20were%20abundant%20and%20included%20uncapped%20food%20for%20staff%20and%20their%20guests%2C%20a%20%2475%20morale%20budget%20per%20employee%20each%20quarter%2C%20a%20generous%20reward%20system%2C%20and%20a%20bonus%20day%20a%20month%20to%20recharge.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20joined%20one%20of%20my%20mentors%20said%2C%20'Welcome%20to%20your%20early%20retirement%20job%2C'%26quot%3B%20a%20current%20employee%20who%20has%20been%20at%20the%20company%20for%20several%20years%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20never%20trying%20to%20build%20out%20the%20newest%20tech%20or%20catch%20the%20latest%20trend%20and%20as%20a%20result%2C%20working%20there%20meant%20you%20weren't%20trying%20to%20accomplish%20things.%20If%20you%20were%2C%20you'd%20be%20trying%20to%20join%20Google%20or%20Apple%2C%26quot%3B%20this%20person%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETightening%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bgolden%20days%26quot%3B%20officially%20came%20to%20an%20end%20in%20early%202023%2C%20some%20workers%20said%2C%20and%20culminated%20in%20layoffs%20by%20year-end.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20February%2C%20engineering%20managers%20were%20instructed%20to%20place%20about%2010%25%20of%20their%20reports%20on%20performance-improvement%20plans%2C%20called%20%26quot%3BPIP%26quot%3B%20for%20short%2C%20nine%20of%20the%20current%20and%20former%20employees%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20said.%20PIPs%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-workers-sick-of-grind-search-low-stress-jobs-burnout-2023-5%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecome%20increasingly%20common%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20major%20tech%20firms%20and%20can%20be%20a%20precursor%20for%20being%20let%20go.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeverich%20said%20the%20company%20never%20gave%20managers%20a%20mandate%20to%20put%20a%20certain%20percentage%20of%20employees%20on%20a%20PIP.%20The%20spokesperson%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20whether%20the%20number%20of%20employees%20placed%20on%20PIPs%20has%20increased%20over%20the%20last%C2%A0year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn%20rates%20its%20workers%20on%20a%20scale%20of%20one%20to%20five%2C%20seven%20workers%20told%20BI.%20A%20five%20rating%20means%20the%20worker%20is%20exceeding%20expectations%2C%20while%20a%20one%20or%20a%20two%20is%20an%20opportunity%20for%20a%20manager%20to%20put%20the%20individual%20on%20a%20PIP%2C%20they%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%202023%2C%20workers%20could%20get%20a%20%26quot%3Bsoft%20three%26quot%3B%20if%20they%20had%20a%20good%20relationship%20with%20their%20boss%2C%20a%20former%20engineering%20manager%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20those%20workers%20are%20receiving%20one%20and%20two%20ratings%2C%20two%20former%20managers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20told%20to%20find%20people%20to%20put%20on%20PIP%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20engineering%20manager%20said.%C2%A0%26quot%3BI%20had%20to%20find%20two%20people%20on%20my%20team%20to%20put%20on%20a%20two%20rating.%20Nobody%20was%20a%20two%20but%20we%20had%20to%20force%20put%20somebody%20on%20a%20two.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20current%20engineering%20manager%20added%20that%20the%20goalposts%20for%20performance%20reviews%20had%20shifted.%20%26quot%3BIn%20this%20new%20environment%20over%20the%20last%20year%2C%20three%20is%20scarier%20than%20it%20was%20before%20because%20now%20the%20threat%20of%20PIPs%20is%20viable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shift%20echoes%20changes%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20LinkedIn's%20parent%20company.%20In%202023%2C%20Microsoft%20introduced%20a%20new%20employee-rating%20system%20only%20visible%20to%20managers%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-employee-rating-system-performance-2023-9%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBI%20first%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Managers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-new-employee-review-system-stack-ranking-2023-9%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewere%20also%20told%20to%20limit%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20number%20of%20workers%20hitting%20the%20top%20rating.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20a%20Microsoft%20spokesperson%20said%20there%20were%20no%20requirements%20for%20managers%20to%20give%20employees%20a%20lower%20ranking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20LinkedIn%20workers%20said%20that%20a%20few%20months%20after%20the%20company%20began%20putting%20more%20people%20on%20PIPs%2C%20LinkedIn%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20engineering%20Mohak%20Shroff%20told%20staff%20in%20an%20all-hands%20meeting%20that%20LinkedIn%20planned%20to%20change%20its%20engineering%20culture%20to%20become%20more%20%26quot%3Bscrappy%26quot%3B%20and%20embody%20the%20mantra%20of%20%26quot%3Bmove%20fast%20and%20break%20things.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20'scrappy'%20became%20an%20internal%20joke%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20engineer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerks%20were%20also%20scaled%20back.%20The%20company%20had%20introduced%20%26quot%3Blift-up%20days%26quot%3B%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20one%20Friday%20a%20month%20where%20no%20meetings%20were%20held%20and%20staff%20could%20choose%20how%20they%20wanted%20to%20spend%20the%20day.%20Some%20workers%20said%20staff%20could%20spend%20the%20day%20pursuing%20leisure%20activities.%20The%20perk%20is%20no%20longer%20available%20today%2C%20four%20people%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn's%20revenue%20growth%20was%20also%20decelerating.%20In%20the%202022%20fiscal%20year%2C%20LinkedIn's%20revenue%20had%20climbed%2034%25%20from%20the%20previous%20year.%20That%20fell%20to%2010%25%20year-over-year%20growth%20in%20the%20fiscal%20year%20for%202023.%20For%20its%20first%20quarter%202024%20earnings%2C%20the%20company%20said%20it%20anticipates%20revenue%20growth%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Bmid-single%20digits.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20sprint%20to%20release%20AI%20products%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShroff's%20declaration%20that%20LinkedIn's%20culture%20should%20become%20more%20scrappy%20coincided%20with%20an%20increased%20focus%20on%20AI%20across%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20as%20the%20launch%20of%20ChatGPT%20kicked%20off%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chaos-ai-arms-race-competitors-ethics-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAI%20arms%20race%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20began%20pushing%20hard%20to%20roll%20out%20AI%20products%20quickly%2C%20six%20workers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEveryone%20I've%20talked%20to%20that%20has%20worked%20on%20it%20%5BAI%5D%20is%20being%20way%20overworked%20and%20all%20burned%20out%20because%20it's%20being%20pushed%20so%20heavily%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20current%20engineer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.linkedin.com%2F2023%2Foctober%2FNew_AI_Powered_Features_for_Businesses%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Erolled%20out%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20AI-powered%20%26quot%3BCoaching%20Experience%26quot%3B%20in%20October%202023%2C%20along%20with%20a%20tool%20to%20help%20recruiters%20find%20candidates%20faster.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reasoning%20behind%20some%20company%20decisions%20on%20AI%20is%20not%20always%20clear%20to%20the%20rank%20and%20file%2C%20the%20engineer%20added%2C%20with%20workers%20joking%20that%20decisions%20are%20%26quot%3Bbased%20on%20vibes.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BThe%20culture%20shifted%20without%20question%20in%20the%20last%20year%20or%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20engineer%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20at%20Amazon%2C%20Google%2C%20or%20an%20AI%20startup%20trying%20to%20solve%20the%20most%20hard-hitting%2C%20high-velocity%20technical%20challenges%20in%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20LinkedIn.%20That%20was%20always%20fine%20because%20we%20had%20one%20of%20the%20least%20evil%20technical%20products%2C%20we%20connect%20people.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn%20spokesperson%20Leverich%20said%20the%20company's%20new%20AI%20products%20%26quot%3Ball%20ladder%20up%20to%20our%20vision%20of%20creating%20economic%20opportunity%20for%20every%20member%20of%20the%20global%20workforce.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETensions%20spilled%20into%20all-hands%20spat%20with%20CEO%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ryan%20Roslansky%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5eda600b5af6cc57066815b6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELinkedIn%20CEO%20Ryan%20Roslansky.%3Cp%3EKelly%20Sullivan%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20LinkedIn%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn's%20pivot%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bscrappy%26quot%3B%20engineering%20culture%20coincided%20with%20a%20downward%20trend%20in%20employee%20morale%2C%20seven%20people%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20pointed%20to%20the%20company's%20quarterly%20employee%20survey%2C%20which%20is%20shared%20on%20a%20team-by-team%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20survey%20showed%20people%20didn't%20understand%20the%20vision%20of%20LinkedIn%20and%20they%20weren't%20excited%20to%20come%20into%20work%20anymore%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20worker%20present%20for%20internal%20discussions%20on%20the%20survey%20said%2C%20commenting%20on%20the%20most%20recent%20autumn%20poll.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20frustration%20spilled%20into%20the%20company's%20September%20all-hands%2C%20held%20by%20CEO%20Ryan%20Roslansky%2C%20shortly%20before%20hundreds%20of%20staff%20got%20cut.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EDuring%20Roslansky's%20Q%26amp%3BA%2C%20one%20employee%20claimed%20publicly%20that%20he'd%20faced%20retaliation%20and%20discrimination%20by%20a%20manager%2C%20and%20complained%20that%20HR%20hadn't%20responded%2C%20according%20to%20a%20transcript%20of%20the%20meeting%20seen%20by%20BI.%20Roslanksy%20responded%20and%20suggested%20the%20worker%20discuss%20the%20issue%20one-on-one%2C%20people%20who%20attended%20the%20Q%26amp%3BA%20said.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BThat%20all-hands%20meeting%20made%20people%20even%20more%20nervous%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20worker%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-layoffs-job-cuts-email-employees-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E668%20employees%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20went%20on%20to%20lose%20their%20jobs%20in%20the%20October%20layoffs.%20Adding%20salt%20to%20the%20wound%2C%20a%20list%20of%20around%20500%20people%20impacted%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-employees-learned-layoffs-early-list-blind-post-2023-10%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eleaked%20to%20the%20workplace-discussion%20app%20Blind%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20layoffs%20have%20definitely%20had%20a%20chilling%20effect%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20worker%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20made%20people%20realize%20that%20the%20company%20has%20higher%20standards%20of%20accountability.%20I%20think%20people%20had%20become%20used%20to%20a%20company%20that%20was%20incredibly%20permissive%20of%20a%20lower%20work%20ethic.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESome%20workers%20think%20the%20debloating%20was%20overdue%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20workers%20see%20the%20layoffs%20and%20increased%20focus%20on%20performance%20as%20a%20much-needed%20course%20correction.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BThere%20were%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20that%20joined%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20but%20we%20remained%20relatively%20stagnant%20in%20terms%20of%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20engineer%20said.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20would%20work%20for%20months%20on%20a%20new%20feature%20and%20it%20would%20get%20zero%20adoption.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20LinkedIn%20isn't%20alone%20in%20pushing%20for%20growth%20and%20efficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20three%20years%20of%20pandemic%20growth%2C%20most%20of%20the%20major%20US%20tech%20firms%20laid%20off%20staff%20and%20were%20rewarded%20by%20investors%20for%20focusing%20on%20efficiency%20over%20expansion.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BThe%20broadly%20defined%20tech%20industry%20mistakenly%20assumed%20that%20the%20growth%20they%20saw%20in%202021%20could%20persist%2C%20but%20it%20was%20always%20unlikely%20to%20occur%2C%26quot%3B%20Madison%20and%20Hall%20analyst%20Brian%20Wieser%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20reality%20set%20in%20%E2%80%94%20amplified%20by%20the%20realization%20of%20higher%20interest%20rates%20and%20overstated%20concerns%20about%20an%20economic%20downturn%2C%20which%20of%20course%20never%20happened%20%E2%80%94%20they%20started%20reducing%20spending%20on%20many%20activities.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%2C%20LinkedIn's%20parent%20company%2C%20has%20seen%20its%20share%20price%20rise%2061.2%25%20in%20the%20last%20year.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BWe'd%20become%20bloated%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20were%20spinning%20their%20wheels%20for%20a%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20current%20employee%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20needed%