ople.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20case%20against%20Israel%20at%20the%20ICJ%20is%20one%20of%20three%20currently%20before%20the%20top%20United%20Nations%20(UN)%20court%2C%20often%20described%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9CWorld%20Court.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20cases%20include%20one%20that%20was%20filed%20by%20Ukraine%20shortly%20after%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%2C%20accusing%20Moscow%20of%20launching%20the%20military%20operation%20based%20on%20trumped-up%20claims%20of%20genocide%2C%20and%20in%20turn%20accusing%20Russia%20of%20planning%20acts%20of%20genocide%20in%20Ukraine%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20in%20November%202019%2C%20Gambia%20filed%20a%20case%20at%20the%20ICJ%20on%20behalf%20of%20Muslim%20nations.%20It%20accuses%20Myanmar%20of%20genocide%20against%20the%20Rohingya%20Muslim%20minority.%20Gambia%20is%20predominantly%20Muslim%20and%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Organisation%20of%20Islamic%20Cooperation%20(OIC)%2C%20which%20boasts%20about%2030%20African%20member%20states%20and%20is%20backing%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20case%20against%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20during%20an%20early%20stage%20of%20proceedings%2C%20the%20ICJ%20ruled%20in%20favour%20of%20Gambia%2C%20ordering%20Myanmar%20to%20%E2%80%9Ctake%20all%20measures%20within%20its%20power%E2%80%9D%20to%20prevent%20the%20commission%20of%20acts%20defined%20in%20the%20convention%20%E2%80%93%20including%20ensuring%20that%20its%20military%20and%20any%20irregular%20armed%20units%20refrain%20from%20committing%20such%20acts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20the%20South%20African%20and%20Gambian%20cases%20differ%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSouth%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20motivations%20might%20be%20very%20different%20from%20The%20Gambia%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Thijs%20Bouwgnegt%2C%20senior%20researcher%20at%20the%20NIOD%20Institute%20for%20War%2C%20Holocaust%20and%20Genocide%20Studies%20in%20Amsterdam%2C%20adding%20that%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20record%20of%2046%20years%20of%20legislated%20apartheid%20might%20have%20played%20a%20vital%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%2084-page%20application%2C%20South%20Africa%20stresses%20some%20similarities%20they%20see%20with%20the%20Palestinian%20territories.%20Israel%20rejects%20any%20suggestions%20of%20similarities%20with%20apartheid%2C%20and%20the%20claim%20is%20highly%20contentious%20globally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20very%20good%20move%20because%20it%20reflects%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20advocating%20for%20human%20rights%20and%20supporting%20those%20affected%20by%20conflict%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dija%20Jawo%2C%20a%20Gambian%20blogger%2C%20told%20DW.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJawo%20also%20said%20that%20the%20rights%20of%20those%20living%20through%20apartheid%20in%20South%20Africa%20were%20violated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSome%20were%20killed%2C%20and%20some%20were%20imprisoned%20like%20Nelson%20Mandela%20for%20over%20two%20decades.%20So%20they%20know%20what%20the%20Gazans%20are%20going%20through%2C%E2%80%9D%20claimed%20Jawo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJewish%20South%20Africans%20are%20disappointed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20South%20African%20Jewish%20Board%20of%20Deputies%20(SAJBD)%20has%20criticised%20the%20South%20African%20government%20for%20taking%20Israel%20to%20the%20ICJ.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20not%20seen%20this%20being%20done%20by%20South%20Africa%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20conflict%2C%20in%20relation%20to%20horrific%20conflicts%20occurring%20throughout%20Africa%2C%20including%20at%20the%20moment%20in%20the%20Congo%20and%20in%20the%20Sudan%2C%E2%80%9D%20Karen%20Milner%2C%20the%20national%20chair%20of%20the%20SAJBD%2C%20told%20DW.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20case%20arose%20after%20Israel%20launched%20its%20offensive%20in%20Gaza%20after%20Hamas%20%E2%80%93%20which%20has%20been%20recognised%20as%20a%20terrorist%20group%20by%20the%20EU%2C%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Germany%20and%20others%2C%20but%20not%20South%20Africa%20%E2%80%93%20carried%20out%20a%20series%20of%20major%20terror%20attacks%20in%20southern%20Israel%20on%20October%207%2C%20killing%20some%201%2C200%20people%20and%20taking%20more%20than%20200%20hostages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETens%20of%20thousands%20of%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza%20have%20since%20been%20killed%20in%20the%20fighting%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Hamas-run%20Health%20Ministry%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20Nations%20has%20warned%20that%20the%20humanitarian%20situation%20in%20Gaza%20is%20deteriorating.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSouth%20Africa%20could%20have%20chosen%20a%20route%20which%20would%20have%20led%20to%20peace%2C%E2%80%9D%20Milner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20stressed%20that%20South%20Africa%20could%20have%20specifically%20demanded%20and%20placed%20pressure%20on%20Hamas%20to%20release%20the%20hostages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CInstead%2C%20they%20have%20engaged%20in%20an%20extremely%20expensive%2C%20extensive%20legal%20process%20which%20is%20unlikely%20to%20have%20any%20real%20impact%20ultimately%20on%20the%20conclusion%20of%20this%20war.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1948%20UN%20Genocide%20Convention%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20complaint%20filed%20at%20the%20ICJ%2C%20South%20Africa%20invoked%20the%201948%20UN%20Convention%20on%20the%20Prevention%20and%20punishment%20of%20the%20Crime%20of%20Genocide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20crime%20of%20genocide%20under%20international%20law%20means%20specific%20acts%20done%20with%20the%20intent%20to%20destroy%20members%20of%20a%20national%2C%20racial%2C%20ethnic%2C%20or%20religious%20group.%20As%20such%2C%20in%20whole%20or%20in%20part%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bouwgnegt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%20has%20firmly%20rejected%20the%20genocide%20allegations%20and%20vowed%20to%20fight%20them%20at%20the%20ICJ.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsraeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%2C%20President%20Isaac%20Herzog%2C%20and%20other%20senior%20Israeli%20officials%20have%20made%20strong%20public%20statements%20accusing%20South%20Africa%20of%20%E2%80%9Cblood%20libel%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20or%20antisemitism%20%E2%80%93%20the%20term%20for%20hostility%20or%20prejudice%20against%20Jewish%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addressing%20the%20opening%20hearing%20at%20the%20ICJ%20on%20Thursday%2C%20South%20African%20advocate%20Tembeka%20Ngcukaitobi%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9CIsrael%20has%20a%20genocidal%20intent%20against%20the%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%E2%80%99s%20legal%20representatives%20are%20due%20to%20address%20the%20ICJ%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDW%20asked%20Michael%20Becker%2C%20Assistant%20Professor%20of%20International%20Human%20Rights%20Law%20at%20Trinity%20College%20Dublin%2C%20about%20the%20allegation%20of%20%E2%80%9Cgenocidal%20intent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20very%20difficult%20to%20establish%20what%E2%80%99s%20referred%20to%20as%20genocidal%20intent%2C%E2%80%9D%20Becker%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThat%20question%20of%20whether%20the%20requisite%20level%20of%20intent%20is%20present%20is%20difficult%20to%20show%20in%20a%20court%20of%20law.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Becker%20and%20Bouwgnegt%20agree%20that%20establishing%20whether%20or%20not%20Israel%20has%20committed%20or%20is%20committing%20genocide%20was%20a%20difficult%20question%20that%20could%20take%20many%20years%20to%20answer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20one%20of%20the%20most%20challenging%20crimes%20to%20prove%20in%20a%20court%20of%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bouwgnegt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20is%20South%20Africa%20taking%20Israel%20to%20court%20for%20genocide%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESankulleh%20Janko%20(in%20Banjul)%2C%20Thuso%20Khumalo%20(in%20Johannesburg)%20and%20Lucia%20Schulten%20(in%20The%20Hague)%20contributed%20to%20this%20article.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3